<div class="content"><div class="main large"><h3>Storybot Modals</h3>
  <p>
    Modals have a header (inside <i>.modal-header</i>), body (inside <i>.modal-body</i>), and footer (inside <i>.modal-footer</i>), all of which are wrapped in the <i>modal-content</i> class. The element used to trigger the modal uses <i>data-toggle="modal"</i> and <i>data-target</i> to launch the associated modal. The <i>modal-dialog</i> class is used to position the modal on the screen.<br>
    Be sure to include the <i>modal-footer</i> div even if it is empty to ensure the modal has correct padding.
    <br><br>
    Modals that are smaller than the browser viewport will be centered in the middle of the screen. Modals that are larger, will take up the screen and scroll.
    <br><br>
    Include the class <i>fade</i> to fade the backdrop in and out when showing the modal and it's animation.<br>
    Include the attribute <i>data-dismiss="modal"</i> in a button to dismiss the modal when clicked.
    <br><br>
  </p>

  <p>To toggle a modal through javascript:</p>
<code><pre>
$('#myh1HeadingModal').modal('toggle');
</pre></code>
  <p>
    Storybot modals have a distinct look to them. Use the classes <i>white</i> or <i>blue</i> to use the preset modals. 
    Use the class <i>btn-close</i> for the unique round close button.
  </p>
<code><pre>
&lt;a class="btn green" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myh1HeadingModal">
  Blue Modal
&lt;/a>

&lt;div class="modal blue fade" id="myh1HeadingModal" tabindex="-1">

  &lt;div class="modal-dialog">
    &lt;div class="modal-content">

      &lt;a class="close btn-close blue" data-dismiss="modal">
        &lt;i class="fa fa-times fa-fw fa-2x">&lt;/i>
      &lt;/a>

      &lt;div class="modal-header">
        &lt;h1 id="h1Heading">H1 Heading&lt;/h1>
      &lt;/div>

      &lt;div class="modal-body">
        &lt;p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur...&lt;/p>
      &lt;/div>

      &lt;div class="modal-footer">
        &lt;a class="btn blue" data-dismiss="modal">Button&lt;/a>
      &lt;/div>

    &lt;/div>
  &lt;/div>

&lt;/div> 
</pre></code>
</div></div>

